SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 771
By Seal
A RESOLUTION to commend and congratulate Cooper Newman
of Sevier County High School upon receiving the
2025 Tennessee Titans Mr. Football Award for
Division I, Class 5A.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this General Assembly should specially
recognize those outstanding young athletes who, through their superlative efforts and
achievements in high school football, have distinguished themselves as true champions of the
sport; and
WHEREAS, one such remarkable individual is Cooper Newman, a junior at Sevier
County High School, who was recently honored with the 2025 Tennessee Titans Mr. Football
Award for Division I, Class 5A; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Newman, who has committed himself to the pursuit of excellence both
on the gridiron and in the classroom while displaying outstanding character as a member of the
Sevier County High School Smoky Bears, was chosen by a committee of sportswriters to
receive the award, for which he was nominated by coaches and members of the media; and
WHEREAS, a versatile and talented player, Cooper Newman excelled as a quarterback
for the Smoky Bears, finishing the season with 269 completions on 367 attempts, for a 73
percent completion rate, which is good for ninth place in the TSSAA record books for single-
season completions; and
WHEREAS, he threw for 45 touchdowns, putting him sixth in single-season completions
for the TSSAA, and amassed 3,705 yards passing for the season while indelibly marking his
name in the Sevier County High School record books in multiple categories, including the
school's single-season passing record; and
SJR0771
011745
- 1 -

WHEREAS, no stranger to awards and accolades, Cooper Newman was also named the
All-Region Player of the Year for Region 1-5A for his outstanding performance during this past
season; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Newman is a winner both on and off the field of play, and his dedication
to excellence is clearly deserving of the respect, admiration, and commendation of this General
Assembly; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING, that we hereby commend and congratulate Cooper
Newman of Sevier County High School upon his receipt of the 2025 Tennessee Titans Mr.
Football Award for Division I, Class 5A and extend to him our best wishes for his every future
success.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
